  "rationale": "A single cinematic stack-fullbleed hero: one edge-to-edge staircase photograph on the sanctioned inverse surface, with the didone colossal display title 'Everything in one place' overlaid as the ONE legal text-on-media (marked sanctioned) \u2014 the hero bookend's sole exception to no-text-on-photos. The lone brand accent rides the display title on this inverse band; the two CTAs are typographic arrow/slash links (never buttons). Eyebrow, lede and actions anchor left/asymmetric per no-centered-everything's editorial exception while the poster-scale title carries the monumental first impression. Adapted from hero-split-media-copy but recomposed to a full-bleed single-image treatment as the variety directive requires; no footer added to keep the opening bookend singular and striking."
